channel.name: The Fun Squad
channel.description:
The Fun Squad is a family friendly, fun adventure channel for all ages. FUN is our superpower! Whether it’s a fun story, a music video or a game, The Fun Squad's goal is to give the world fun and entertaining videos! We love to play fun characters: a superhero, a spy or a sneaky ninja. The Fun Squad will make you laugh as they recreate movies, solve a mystery, compete in girls vs boys games, play jokes, play games, act as a superhero, share a birthday pretend to be in another place. Brandon, Sarah and the kids are skilled singers and spread optimism through: a music video, a cover song or an official music video. The funny kids of the Fun Squad (Jack & Jazzy (twins), Kade, Kalia and Kyler Skye) are fun and exciting with unique personalities. The Fun Squad motto is: Never Grow Up! Come join the Fun Squad by watching family friendly fun videos for all ages! Welcome to the Official Fun Squad YouTube channel!
Business Email:  Admin@TheFunSquad.com
Fan email:  FanMail@TheFunSquad.com

videos.title: Pause Remote With Halloween Jokes!
videos.description:
Pause Remote With Halloween Jokes! Kade stumbles upon the long-lost Pause Remote in his house, a relic from the Fun Squad’s past jokes. Instead of putting it back, he decides to cause some mischief! Watch as Kade pulls off hilarious jokes on Jazzy and Jack, from a spooky sandwich to fun jump scares with a mask. But when Jack and Jazzy find out about the remote, the tables turn, and the Fun Squad teams up for the ultimate revenge joke on Kade. Will Kade survive the final joke? Or will he be scared? Watch until the end for an epic twist with Kyler! Happy Halloween, Fun Squad!

videos.description:

We had so much fun recreating this classic Halloween song, THIS IS HALLOWEEN! We had the whole entire Fun Squad and cast in this awesome Halloween Town set! Thanks to everyone in this video! It turned out amazing! The Fun Squad loves to sing and dance and have a blast singing covers and original songs and all things music! Watch as Jack The Pumpkin King turns into Jack Skelington!
Thanks to Becky Willard at VoxFox Studios and Daniel at Blomberg Music Productions for the musical arrangement!

videos.description:

The remaining 8 men and 4 women go head-to-head to see who will take top honors in this year's final event in the Tordrillo Mountains. This small range can be found between the Chigmit and Aleutian Ranges, 75 miles west-northwest and visible from Anchorage. Heavily glaciated and primarily volcanic, the Tords are arguably one of the best venues on the planet for riders to push the boundaries of big mountain freestyle riding.

videos.title: GoPro: HERO10 Black | HyperSmooth 4.0
videos.description:
This in-camera, electronic video stabilization has reset the bar and continues to be available across all resolutions and frame rates. Flexibility is at your fingertips with 3 levels of performance options— “Standard”, “High”, and “Boost”. Our new GP2 processor unlocks “High” in the camera’s top resolutions, increasing your FOV by reducing the crop factor in the “Linear + HL” Digital Lens. When toggled, in-camera horizon leveling keeps your footage perfectly straight and its tilt limit has been increased from 27° to 45° in select modes. Whatever the activity, HyperSmooth 4.0 will keep your action more watchable.

videos.title: All Performances of Portuguese Superstar FERNANDO DANIEL on The Voice
videos.description:
Fernando Daniel’s journey might be one of the most remarkable in The Voice’s history. His Blind Audition in 2016 went viral, leading him to win the season. Just five years later, he was back on The Voice — but this time as a coach on The Voice Kids Portugal. And by 2023, he also sat down in the coach chair in the main season of The Voice Portugal! Enjoy this compilation of his unforgettable moments on The Voice Portugal, and let us know in the comments below which performance is your favorite! 👇
P.S. Sorry for the low quality in the first part of this video. Unfortunately, no better quality is available, but the quality will improve as the video progresses.

channel.name: Mariah Carey
channel.description:
Welcome to Mariah Carey's official YouTube channel!

MARIAH CAREY is the best-selling female artist of all time with more than 200 million albums sold to date and 19 Billboard Hot 100 #1 singles (18 self-penned), more than any solo artist in history. Mariah is a singer/songwriter/producer recognized with multiple Grammy Awards, numerous American Music Awards, Billboard's 'Artist of the Decade' Award, the World Music Award for 'World's Best Selling Female Artist of the Millennium' and BMI's 'Icon Award' for her outstanding achievements in songwriting, to name a few – with her distinct five-octave vocal range, prolific songwriting, and producing talent, Mariah is truly the template of the modern pop performance. Mariah's ongoing impact has transcended the music industry to leave an indelible imprint upon the world at large.

videos.title: Cómo bajar los TRIGLICÉRIDOS solo con REMEDIOS CASEROS
videos.description:
Hoy te enseñaré los 5 mejores remedios naturales para bajar los triglicéridos, fácilmente y desde tu propia casa. 
Número 1. El agua de avena con canela
La avena tiene betaglucanos, una fibra soluble muy buena para ti, ya que al tomar avena te ayudará a absorber muchas de las grasas que están atrapadas en tu intestino, pero si la juntas con un poco de canela, con sus antioxidantes tendrás la receta perfecta para disminuir los triglicéridos y el colesterol. Y para prepararla solo necesitarás dejar reposar en agua por toda la noche media taza de avena en hojuelas con una rama de canela. Tómala todos los días y preferiblemente en ayunas. Pero lo mejor de todo es que también la avena normal del desayuno que ya preparas, cumple la misma función con un poco de canela en polvo encima.
Número 2. La Alcachofa
La alcachofa tiene cinarina, una sustancia ideal para todo lo que se trate de combatir el colesterol en tu cuerpo y hacer que tu organismo trabaje mejor. La mejor forma de consumirlas es al vapor y cocidas, después de haberla limpiado y recortado. Con la alcachofa vas a prevenir la obesidad, los infartos y hasta la diabetes. También puedes usar como un té poderoso una taza del agua que queda después de hervir las alcachofas y tomar hasta tres veces al día.
Número 3. La albahaca
La albahaca tiene aceites esenciales muy ricos en antioxidantes que pueden ayudarte a combatir el daño de los triglicéridos altos. Para preparar el té de albahaca coloca una taza de agua a hervir y luego añade media cucharada de albahaca. Tapa y deja reposar durante 5 a 10 minutos, por último, cuela y bebe de 2 a 3 tazas de té por día. Y no estaría mal añadirle de vez en cuando a tus comidas, algunas hojas de albahaca frescas, porque fortalecerá mucho tu cuerpo y a la larga te traerá más salud.
Número 4. El té de cúrcuma
La cúrcuma tiene otros antioxidantes que en el mundo son muy usados para algunas de las mejores medicinas para tu cuerpo y que eliminarán la grasa y las toxinas que estén en tu organismo. Para preparar el té de cúrcuma, coloca una taza de agua a hervir y luego añade una cucharadita de cúrcuma. Tapa y deja reposar durante 5 a 10 minutos, por último, cuela y bebe hasta 3 tazas de té por día.

Número 5. El té verde
Y por último, si tienes té verde en tu casa, empieza a tomarlo más seguido, porque el té verde tiene catequinas, flavonoides y muchos otros compuestos antioxidantes que te ayudarán a disminuir los niveles de colesterol malo y triglicéridos en la sangre. Puedes tomarte hasta 3 tazas de té verde al día para resultados rápidos. Cada vez hay más estudios que demuestran lo bueno que es y además, previene el envejecimiento y mejora tus defensas.
Por supuesto, no es recomendable tomar cualquiera de estas recetas en exceso, ni combinarlas todas en un solo día. Recuerda siempre consultar con tu médico personal antes de consumir cualquiera de estos ingredientes.

videos.title: LA MÚSICA DEL CHAVO FUE ESCRITA HACE 200 AÑOS? #elchavodelocho
videos.description:
La música de El Chavo del Ocho es una de las más icónicas en la televisión latinoamericana. Aunque la canción de introducción fue adaptada por el compositor francés Jean-Jacques Perrey a partir de una pieza de Beethoven llamada "La Marcha Turca", la música de apertura original del programa también fue compuesta por Ludwig van Beethoven en honor a la obra "Las Ruinas de Atenas". La canción "The Elephant Never Forgets" de Perrey se convirtió en el opening de la serie y fue utilizada sin dar crédito al autor, lo que resultó en una demanda millonaria en 2010. A pesar de esto, la música sigue siendo muy popular en toda Latinoamérica.

videos.title: Cura la TOS con REMEDIOS CASEROS |☕️🌿 ¿Qué tomar para EXPULSAR LAS FLEMAS? Lunacreciente
videos.description:
Hoy te enseñaré 3 remedios caseros para eliminar la tos rápidamente y cómo prepararlos. 
Número 1. Agua con sal
Si estás tosiendo con flemas y arrastrando la mucosidad cada vez que toses, es porque tienes tos productiva. Necesitas sacarte toda esa flema y puedes hacerlo muy fácilmente haciendo gárgaras con agua y sal. Disuelve media cucharadita de sal en un vaso con agua caliente, deja que enfríe un poco y ahora si puedes hacer gárgaras por algunos minutos con esta solución, luego escupirla y enjuagar bien. Esta mezcla va a reducir las flemas y la mucosidad que está atrapada, aliviará la irritación de la garganta y hará que dejes de toser luego de un rato de haber hecho las gárgaras.
Número 2. La miel
Si te pica mucho la garganta y no tienes casi nada de moco, pero no paras de toser ni por la noche, tienes tos seca… Y lo mejor para quitarla es la miel. Tómate una cucharada de miel, o también puedes diluirla en agua, leche o bebidas que sean buenas para la tos seca como el jugo de naranja, el té de jengibre, el té de cúrcuma y el té de menta. La viscosidad de la miel crea una capa que te calma y protege de la irritación. La miel es antibiótica, antibacteriana y expectorante, que también te ayudará a expulsar toda esa flema que no ha podido salir por la tos seca para que luego no sigas tosiendo.
Número 3. El agua
Siempre que tengas tos, sin importar del tipo que sea, necesitas mantenerte bien hidratado. Tomar suficiente agua, especialmente si está a temperatura ambiente y no fría, va a aliviar casi todos los tipos de síntomas que puede tener la tos y los resfriados, porque desinflama, refresca y limpia tu garganta al igual que otras partes importantes de tu cuerpo que influyen en tu recuperación contra las enfermedades. Y por supuesto los caldos suaves, las infusiones de hierbas, los jugos de frutas y otras bebidas calientes, te hidratarán tanto como el agua y te aliviarán cuando más lo necesitas.
Recuerda siempre consultar con tu médico personal antes de ejecutar alguna de estas recomendaciones

videos.title: AGUACATE o PALTA 🥑 Beneficios de su SEMILLA y cómo consumirla en Té.
videos.description:
Hoy te enseñaré beneficios de la semilla de palta o aguacate para tu salud. Al final del vídeo te enseñaré a preparar el té de esta semilla, así como el polvo para aprovechar todas sus propiedades.
Número 1. Te da más años de vida
La semilla del aguacate te hace ver y sentir más joven. Sus flavonoides y antioxidantes detienen el daño que causan los radicales libres con el paso del tiempo, como las cataratas y afecciones en la vista o darle origen a la hipertensión e incluso el cáncer… Además de desaparecer las arrugas de tu piel, al darle firmeza y juventud. Lo que contiene esta poderosa semilla también tiene la habilidad de reducir el riesgo a sufrir dolores en las articulaciones y enfermedades en los huesos. Consumir la semilla del aguacate le traerá a tu cuerpo la fortaleza que necesita para mantenerte flexible y con una mejor capacidad física.
Número 2. Fortalece el sistema inmune
El flavonol de las semillas del aguacate impulsa al sistema inmune y te ayuda a protegerte de los resfriados y gripe. El ácido fenólico, que es otro de sus componentes, también hace que consumir la semilla de aguacate sea excelente para tratar las alergias e infecciones. Aumentar el consumo de esta semilla te protegerá frente a todo tipo de enfermedades, pero combatirá especialmente las causadas por virus y bacterias.
Número 3. Protege a tu corazón
El aguacate es una gran fuente de grasas monoinsaturadas, también conocidas como las grasas saludables. Estas son muy buenas para el corazón, ya que contienen aminoácidos y fibras dietética. Pero su semilla también puede ayudar a tu cuerpo a bajar los picos de colesterol y a prevenir un gran número de problemas cardiovasculares como los derrames y ataques cardiacos. Además, la semilla de aguacate evita la formación de placa, que es la acumulación de todo el colesterol y las grasas malas, que con el tiempo estrechan y obstruyen las arterias, causando más problemas en todo el cuerpo.
Número 4. Previene el crecimiento de tumores
La mayor parte de los antioxidantes del aguacate se encuentran en su semilla y el flavonol de estas es un antioxidante que sirve también para reducir el crecimiento de los tumores. Se demostró que los extractos que se obtienen del aguacate y sus aceites pueden lograr que las células de leuceima se autodestruyeran. 
Seguramente te estarás preguntando cómo consumo la semilla de aguacate o palta Para preparar la infusión de esta semilla, necesitarás lavar y pelar la piel marrón que tiene encima. Corta en cuatro trozos la semilla y pon los pedazos a hervir con un litro de agua durante 20 minutos. Apaga, deja enfriar, retira la semilla y ya podrás disfrutar de esta poderosa infusión. Te recomiendo tomar dos tazas al día acompañadas del endulzante natural de tu preferencia, como por ejemplo la miel. Guarda el restante de la bebida en un envase o una jarra con tapa dentro del refrigerador. Otro método es rayando la semilla luego de haberla pelado y dejando secar la ralladura al sol o tostándola en un sartén a fuego muy bajo hasta que se haya secado por completo. Una vez que tengas la ralladura, deja una cucharada de la misma por unos 10 minutos dentro de una taza de agua caliente. Podrás preparar la infusión sin ningún problema y disfrutarás de sus propiedades. Por último, para preparar el polvo de esta semilla utiliza el anterior método para secar la ralladura y luego tritura esta ralladura para obtener el polvo. Ahora podrás utilizarlo como un condimento de grandes beneficios para tus caldos, sopas ensaladas y muchos otros platos e incluso puedes aplicar sobre tu piel este polvo como si fuese una máscara un exfoliante rejuvenecedor diariamente. El consumo de aguacate o palta no es recomendado para personas que padezcan de algún tipo de problema en el hígado si sufres de alergia a este alimento o tienes dudas sobre su consumo No olvides consultar con tu médico de confianza antes de seguir cualquiera de estas recomendaciones.

videos.title: 🍃El LAUREL le hace esto a tu cuerpo🍃 ¿Cómo‚ aprovechar bien las PROPIEDADES de la hoja de LAUREL?
videos.description:
Al final del vídeo te enseñaré a preparar la infusión de laurel con la que podrás aprovechar al máximo sus propiedades.
Número 1. Fortalece el sistema inmunitario
Al consumir el laurel, se activan las células fagocíticas, que pueden destruir los microrganismos, eliminar las células muertas y otros materiales que tu cuerpo no necesita o pueden hacerte daño. Estas células protectoras se activan con el eugenol que hay en las hojas de laurel, ese es uno de los 81 compuestos buenos para tu salud que contiene esta planta. Actúa como antioxidante y fortalece tu sistema inmune para protegerte contra las infecciones, las gripes, resfriados y de muchas otras enfermedades que pueden afectar tu salud. 
Número 2. Combate la diabetes
Está demostrado que tomar el té de hojas de laurel a diario, podría aliviar o prevenir algunos síntomas que suelen aparecer entre las personas con diabetes tipo dos, como la visión borrosa, las úlceras, el aumento de sed, de apetito y de ganas de orinar. El laurel mejora la función de la insulina y es por eso que puede ser una gran ayuda para ti si sufres de diabetes.
Número 3. Reducen la ansiedad
El laurel es un calmante muy efectivo para esos días pesados y momentos de estrés o ansiedad debido a un aceite muy útil que contienen sus hojas para calmar la mente y reducir el nivel de cortisol en la sangre, que es conocido como linalool. Por eso tomar la infusión de hojas de laurel y añadir esta especia más seguido en tus recetas, hará que puedas dormir mucho mejor y combatir el insomnio, además de volver tus días sean más tranquilos.
Número 4. Es un buen diurético
Esta planta mediterránea es muy beneficiosa para tus riñones gracias a sus poderes diuréticos y sudoríficos. Consumir laurel ayudará a tu cuerpo a que cuando sudes u orines, también puedas eliminar toxinas que estén dentro de tu organismo y son capaces de causarte daños mayores. Además, permite reducir los niveles de ácido úrico en el organismo y por esta razón, es eficaz para tratar problemas circulatorios y enfermedades hepáticas.
Número 5. Funciona como repelente de insectos
El aceite esencial de laurel también es eficaz para repeler a los mosquitos y se ha comprobado que funciona para controlar las poblaciones de garrapatas y ácaros. El olor de esta planta aleja a algunos insectos y puedes aprovecharlo para fumigar tus espacios cada cierto tiempo contra estas plagas, tan solo quemando algunas hojas de laurel en la habitación que quieres desinfectar y usando inciensos o velas hechas de laurel.
Seguramente te estarás preguntando cómo consumo el laurel para aprovechar sus propiedades. Para preparar el té de laurel coloca a hervir a fuego bajo por unos minutos un litro de agua, junto a unas cuatro o cinco cucharadas de hojas de laurel frescas o secas y adicionalmente puedes colocar una ramita o astillas de canela si lo deseas. Retira del fuego, deja reposar hasta que enfríe y ya puedes colar para servir ahora podrás disfrutar de la infusión de esta planta llena de beneficios junto a tu endulzante natural favorito, con una taza en ayunas y otra antes de acostarte. Agregar canela es opcional, pero tiene grandes beneficios como sus antioxidantes mejorar tu estado de ánimo y proteger a tu corazón, que al combinarse con el laurel crean la medicina natural casera perfecta.
No olvides consultar con tu médico de confianza antes de seguir cualquiera de estas recomendaciones.

videos.title: El ACEITE DE OLIVA con LAUREL y ROMERO🌿 beneficios para tu salud 💪🏻 RECETA PASO A PASO
videos.description:
Hoy te enseñaré los beneficios que tiene el aceite de Oliva con Laurel y Romero para tu salud. Además, te enseñaré a prepararlo paso a paso para aprovechar sus propiedades. 
Número 1. Funciona como un colágeno natural
El romero con el aceite de oliva combate el envejecimiento. Gracias a su gran cantidad de antioxidantes y las del aceite de oliva relaja e hidrata tu piel, dándole brillo, frescura, protección y elasticidad. Al combinar el laurel con estos ingredientes; la vitamina A, el calcio, hierro y otras propiedades de esta planta, puedes conseguir que esta receta te sirva para retrasar la aparición de arrugas, obtener colágeno de forma natural por todas las propiedades rejuvenecedoras y restauradoras que se mezclan entre los ingredientes. 
Número 2. Curará tus heridas y aliviará tus músculos
Si tienes una herida, este aceite te ayudará a protegerla y a cicatrizarla más rápido. El romero tiene propiedades antisépticas, que, al combinarse con las propiedades antiinflamatorias del laurel, reducirá el dolor y sanará rápidamente todas las quemaduras, picadas, otros daños en tu piel, y hasta la irritación en áreas íntimas. También puedes aprovechar las propiedades de estas especias y el aceite de oliva para aliviar los molestos dolores en las articulaciones y los músculos. Tan solo masajear con unas gotas de este remedio natural en esa área adolorida te aliviará instantáneamente y mejorará toda la movilidad de tu cuerpo con el tiempo.
Número 3. Cuida tu cerebro y memoria
El aceite de oliva con laurel y romero es muy eficaz contra los dolores de cabeza, tiene una efectividad muy rápida y puede servir incluso para dolores más fuertes como la migraña. Solo necesitarás masajear por unos minutos en el área de la frente con unas gotas del aceite. Esta receta es muy valiosa porque además de quitar el dolor de cabeza puede ayudarte a reducir el estrés y los niveles altos de cortisol en la sangre. Y no solo eso, también te ayuda a mejorar tu memoria y agilidad mental para aprender o solucionar los problemas más rápido, siendo el calmante perfecto para la jornada de trabajo y estudios. Estos beneficios calmantes se obtienen aún más si respiras profundamente varias veces mientras estás cerca del aceite para que tu cuerpo lo absorba rápidamente y a sus propiedades.


A continuación, te enseñaré a preparar el aceite de oliva con laurel y romero
Primero picarás en trozos muy pequeños unas 5 hojas de laurel para obtener aproximadamente una cucharada de esta planta. Ahora sacarás todas las hojitas de 2 ramas pequeñas de romero y necesitarás usar una cucharada de las hojas. Por otro lado, necesitarás 200ml de aceite de oliva que sea específicamente virgen extra, puedes hacerlo llenando exactamente una taza completa del aceite y será aproximadamente la misma cantidad. Ahora si, teniendo estos ingredientes, los colocarás todos a calentar en una olla, pero no la pondrás directamente sobre el fuego, sino que lo harás a baño maría para que no se queme el aceite y pueda funcionar este remedio natural. Para eso colocarás tu olla en otra olla más grande con agua hirviendo a fuego no muy alto. Irás removiendo la mezcla por máximo 30 minutos y luego dejarás la olla con la mezcla reposando lejos del fuego hasta que enfríe. Y para finalizar, ayudándote con un colador, coloca el resultado en un frasco de vidrio con tapa, que deberás guardar fuera de la luz del sol para que mantenga sus propiedades. Este aceite no tiene contraindicaciones y podrás aplicar pequeñas cantidades para masajear en las áreas afectadas a diario si no eres alérgico a ninguno de los ingredientes. Después de 7 días usando esta receta notarás el bien que le hará a tu cuerpo. No olvides consultar con tu médico de confianza antes de aplicar alguno de estos consejos.

videos.title: 🍃Toma Té De HOJAS De GUAYABA y esto te pasará en el cuerpo -Nuevos BENEFICIOS #salud #lunacreciente
videos.description:
Hoy te enseñaré 3 beneficios que seguramente no conocías de las hojas de guayaba para tu salud. Antes de finalizar este vídeo te enseñaré cómo preparar el té con hojas de guayaba, que es la forma de obtener sus mejores propiedades. Recuerda darle me gusta a este vídeo y suscribirte a nuestro canal activando la campanita para que puedas seguir disfrutando de más material como éste
Número 1. Mejora tu digestión y te ayuda a bajar de peso
Si quieres mejorar la salud en tu estómago y sistema digestivo, la guayaba tiene fibras como la pectina que limpia y trae bienestar a tu intestino. Evita que crezcan microbios que puedan producirte enfermedades y malestar. También contiene astringentes como los taninos, que te quitarán la diarrea y aliviarán cualquier indigestión con tan solo tomarte una taza del té que puedes obtener de sus hojas. Y por si fuera poco, esta poderosa fruta puede controlar tu apetito de tal manera que empezarás a bajar de peso al consumirla. Tiene vitaminas, proteínas y minerales que te darán energía, pero su alto contenido en fibra hará que te sientas lleno por más tiempo y no te excedas al comer. 
Número 2. Protege tu vista
La provitamina A que tiene la guayaba, también conocida como beta caroteno, es muy importante para tu cuerpo. Consumir esta fruta más seguido, podrá reforzar tu vista e incluso traerle beneficios a todas las terminaciones nerviosas que tu cuerpo necesita para permitir que tu vista funcione bien, al igual que todos los órganos que necesitan a tu sistema nervioso para garantizar que estos tengan su debido funcionamiento.
Número 3. Cuida tu cerebro y memoria
En muchas partes del mundo, la guayaba es usada por su capacidad para proteger la memoria por las elevadas cantidades de vitamina A que contiene y se han hecho algunas investigaciones sobre eso. Pero lo que si está confirmado es que tomar el té de las hojas de esta fruta te ayudará a mejorar tu capacidad cerebral, ayudar a tu salud mental gracias a que alivia el estrés y la ansiedad e incluso prevenir o tratar muchas de las deficiencias cerebrales que pueden presentarse con el tiempo. Todo esto es gracias a otras propiedades de la fruta como las que protegen a tu sistema nervioso y más vitaminas que contiene como la B6 y la vitamina C. Además, un beneficio sorprendente es que las hojas de la guayaba son especiales para tratar los dolores de cabeza e incluso para tratar la resaca. Masticar sus hojas un poco podría aliviar esos malestares en la cabeza y los mareos.
A continuación, te enseñaré cómo preparar el té de hojas de guayaba
Para elaborar esta receta necesitaremos los siguientes ingredientes: 6 hojas secas de guayaba las cuales debes dejar a la interperie por unos días hasta que tengan una forma arrugada. Canela, que es un ingrediente opcional y por último una taza de agua. Primero debes colocar el agua en una olla que posteriormente pondrás a hervir por un minuto. Cuando termine de hervir, triturarás las hojas y las dejarás caer en el interior de la olla. Notarás que el agua de la olla va cambiando de color, cuando notes esto le pondrás la tapa a la olla y la dejarás reposar por 10 minutos. Al finalizar la espera agrega un poco de canela al gusto, esto se hace para darle un poco más de sabor al té. Por último, traslada el té de guayaba a una taza con un colador para que las hojas no permanezcan en el líquido. Sin duda algunas de las propiedades de algunos alimentos no sólo están en sus frutos, pues, como has notado en este vídeo las hojas también pueden ser bastante beneficiosas para tu salud. Sigue estos consejos, prepara tu té de guayaba y mantente saludable.
No olvides consultar con tu médico de confianza antes de aplicar alguno de estos consejos

Colors!
Time to make them mine! 

Baa, baa, black sheep,
have you any colors?

three bags full.

one bag of black olives,
and here I am. 
A black sheep!

Ooo, ooo, red monkey,
have you any colors?
Yes friend, yes friend,
three bags full.

One bag of red cherries, 
one bag of red bolts,
and here I am. 
A red monkey!

Hop, hop, orange rabbit,
have you any colors?
Yes friend, yes friend,
three bags full.

One bag of orange carrots, 
one bag of orange flowers,
and here I am. 
An orange rabbit! 


Snuffle, snuffle, green hedgehog,
have you any colors?
Yes friend, yes friend,
three bags full.

One bag of green sweets,
one bag of green marbles,
and here I am. 
A green hedgehog!




What happened?    
All our colors have been 
stolen away!

Hoi Poi, Pinkfong!

Yip, yip, rainbow fox,
have you any colors?
Yes friend, yes friend,
three bags full.
 
One bag of rainbow jellies, 
one bag of rainbow cookies,
and here I am. 
I’ve got you!

Hoi Poi, Pinkfong!


Wonderstar friends,
have you any colors?
Yes friend, yes friend!
We all have colors!
Black! 
Red!
Orange!
Green! 
And 
pink!

channel.name: Best Ever Food Review Show
channel.description:
I travel to unique parts of the world on the hunt for the best food each country has to offer and share these stories with you in my videos.

Hey, I’m Sonny! I’m from the US but currently call Vietnam home. I’ve been living in Asia for 10 years and started making food and travel videos to document my experiences. People either enjoyed my undeniable wit or enjoyed watching me eat interesting food like sea penis, and thus Best Ever Food Review Show came to be. 

Best Ever Food Review Show is the first food review show exploring the unique foods of each country with a fresh point of view and a punchy delivery, encouraging empathy and understanding of other cultures along the way. From the best street food to the most insane food markets to...well...yes, sea penis, nothing is off limits (except cucumbers. Cucumbers are off limits). 

I can’t wait to see where this food journey takes us. Don’t forget to subscribe, so we can connect through food and travel and become Bestys!

1️⃣ *MANZURA* https://www.instagram.com/manzura.kafe
📍 Magzhan Jumabayev Street 141
⏰ 12PM - 12AM
👨‍🍳 *Zainullam Zainakhunov* (Chef)

🍛 *DAPANJI w/ RICE* (大盘鸡 “Big Plate of Chicken”)
Sugar, Sichuan pepper, Chopped Chicken, Chili, Anise, Allspice, Cumin, Cloves, Orange Zest, Cardamon, Cinnamon, Chinese Vinegar, Soy Sauce, MSG, Salt, Chili Bean Paste, Tomato Paste, Potatoes, Bell Pepper, Rice & Onion. Cook Spices, Chicken, Pastes, Vegetables, Sauces, Seasonings. Cook Rice w/ Salt & Oil. Garnish Stewed Chicken w/ Onions. Serve w/ Rice.

2️⃣ *KURVANJAN’S HOUSE & BAISAT MARKET*
👨‍🍳 *Kurvanjan* (Chef & Uyghur Activist)


🥟 *UYGHUR GOOSH NAN* (گۆشنان “Meat Bread” - Meat Pie w/ Beef & Onion)
Flour, Beef (Back Leg), Onion, Oil, Salt, Pepper, MSG, Hajo Pepper. Dough (Salt, Flour). Stir, Knead, Roll, Cut, Shape, Flatten. Mix Chopped Beef, Diced Onion, Pepper & MSG. Fill, Fold, Fry until Golden Brown, Steam.

3️⃣ *ASSIGUL’S HOUSE* (Kurvanjan’s Sister)
🧕 *Assigul* (Kurvanjan’s Sister) https://www.instagram.com/food.asi

🍜 *LAGMAN* (Noodles)
Cut Dough (Flour, Egg, Salt) into Pieces. Roll into Long, Thin Strips, Boil. Beef (Back Leg), Oil, Tomatoes, Onion, Jusai (Allium Tuberosum, Garlic Chives), Scallion, Egg, Pepper, Garlic, Salt, Celery, Tomato Paste, MSG, Ground Ginger, Paprika, Sodium Gluconate & Hajo. Stir Fry Beef w/ Vegetables, Seasonings, Add Water. Scramble Salt Mixed Egg, Add Jusai. Pour Broth over Noodles in Bowl. Top w/ Egg & Jusai Mixture.

🫁 *LAMB LUNG stuffed w/ MILK & FLOUR* (“Animalized Tofu” Eaten w/ Sausage)
Knead Dough (Flour, Egg, Salt) w/ Water. Strain, Collect Water. Add Cow Milk, Mix w/ Oil, Egg & Salt. Pour Milk Mixture into Lung w/ Funnel. Blow into Lung, Add more Milk. Seal Opening w/ Potato, Boil. Serve w/ Boiled Sausages (Beef, Rice, Pepper, Onion, Garlic, Cilantro, Sheep Intestine).

Horse Meat Cube Slices, Potato, Onion, Dill, Green Onion, Oil, Salt, Black Pepper. Mix, Cook & Garnish.

Horse Meat marinated with Salt, Pepper & Garlic. Use Horse Bone to create Holes in the Horse Intestine. Stuff into the Intestines, then Cut and Tie them securely with String.

🍜 *NOODLES*
Eggs, Wheat Flour, Salt, Water, Flour. Mix, Rest, Knead, Roll, the Cut. Boil with Beshbarmak.

🐴 *BESHBARMAK*
Kazy (horse sausage), Horse meat (back leg meat and ribs), Horse stomach & ribs, Garlic, Salt, Black pepper, Carrots, Potatoes. Clean ingredients & Mix spices. Stuff the Horse Stomach. Slow cook with Kazan Pot.

⏰ 8 AM - 7 PM
👩🏾‍🍳 *Nana Ama* (Owner)


🐟 *FRIED TILAPIA WITH BANKU* (Boiled Fermented Corn/Cassava Dough)

- BANKU: Corn & Cassava Dough. Water & Salt. Cook Porridge . Knead, Cool.
- TILAPIA: Garlic, Green Habanero, Green Pepper, Chopped Onion, Scallions. Water. Maggi Cubes & Rock Salt. Descale & Cut Fish. Marinate. Fry. Bell Peppers & Onions Topping.

⏰ 10 AM - 6 PM
👩🏾‍🍳 *Mary* (Owner)

💸 *₵23,25 GHS / $1.49 USD* (Each)

🍲 *KONTOMIRE* (Cocoyam Leaves Stew) with Smoked Fish
﻿Boil Cocoyam Leaves, Green Tomatoes & Habanero Pepper. Grind into Paste. Chopped/Sliced Onions. Salt & Maggi powder. Red Palm Oil. Smoked Mackerel Fish & Smoked Tuna Shreds.﻿ Mix. Serve with Boiled Yam.

Deshell, wash, and marinate with powdered pepper, salt, and a Maggi cube. Put the snails on a Kebab stick with onions. Roast or grill. Add the kebab powder and onions.
🐌 *FRESH SNAIL STEW*
Onions, salt, maggi cube. Steam & Boil. Oil fry onions, pepper, fresh tomatoes & tomato paste to oil. Stir & Mix.
🐌 *DEEP-FRIED SNAIL*
Deshell. Salt, Maggi cube, water marinade. Boil & Fry.

📍 M9XG+FP Kumasi, Ghana
⏰ 6 AM - 6 PM
👩🏾‍🍳 *Boahemaa* (Vendor)

📍 *Abena’s chop bar (Chop Bar) - Kejetia Market*
⏰ 6 AM - 7 PM
👩🏾‍🍳 *Abena* (Owner)
🐌 *SNAIL ABUNUABUNU*
﻿Cocoyam leaves, pepper, onions, tomatoes, water. Remove after 5 mins when it softens. Deshell snails. Steam with diced onions, salt and Maggie cube to taste. Pepper and ginger. Mix. Add fresh tomatoes & onions. Wash smoked fish and add to soup. Add prekese (Aiden fruit).
💸 *₵60,34 GHS / $3.86 USD*

🍠 *FUFU* (Pounded Yam/Cassava)
Peel unripe plantain & scrape cassava. Boil. Pound with mortar & pestle. Water.
💸 *₵24,07 GHS / $1.54 USD*

1️⃣ *Bushmeat Street Vendor - Anyiam Village* 
📍 9CPW+WGH Anyinam, Ghana
🙋🏾 *Isaac* (Hunter)

♨️ *DRIED BUSHMEAT*
Take off fur (antelope/dikdik). Roast on open fire. Wash and scrape off blackened skin. Cut open. Take out poop & intestines. Cut into pieces. Mix in pot with other ingredients.
💸 *₵755,62 GHS / $48.31 USD*

2️⃣ *Kejetia Market*
📍 M9XG+FP Kumasi, Ghana
⏰ 6 AM - 6 PM

📍 *Bushmeat Vendor*
⏰ 6 AM - 6 PM
💁🏾‍♂️ *Kofi Manu* (Vendor)


🍖 *SMOKED BUSHMEAT*
Get rid of fur with open fire. Scrape burnt fur. Roast meat. Cut open and chop into pieces for consumption or preservation.
💸 *₵782,06 GHS / $50.00 USD*

📍 *Bushmeat Processor*
⏰ 6 AM - 6 PM
🙋🏾‍♂️ *Ofori Kweku* (Vendor)

📍 *Chop Bar*
⏰ 5 AM - 6 PM
💁🏾‍♀️ *Theresah* (Vendor)

🍚 *OMO TUO (Rice Ball) making + NKATE NKWAN (Groundnut Soup)*
Make groundnut / peanut butter soup. Blend ginger, onions, garlic and boil red pepper, two tomatoes and one onion separately, then blend. Add water. Make soup. Bushmeat, salt, Maggi cubes, tomato paste, fresh tomato, onion, water, diluted groundnut paste, dried fish. Boil in pot. Make rice balls. Water, salt, broken rice, pour groundnut soup over it to serve.
💸 *₵60,22 GHS / $3.85 USD*

🇻🇳 *HO CHI MINH CITY (Saigon, Vietnam)*


*1. Nem chua Bà Chín*
📍 58 Đường Trần Hưng Đao, Hiệp Phú, Quận 9
👨‍🍳 Mr. Hung (Owner)

🥢 *NEM NƯỚNG BÁNH HỎI*
(Grilled Pork Sausage w/Fine Rice Vermicelli)
Lettuce, aromatic herbs, perilla leaves, pickles (carrot & daikon), sliced cucumber, bean sprouts, fine rice vermicelli, sliced grilled pork sausages, scallion oil, and peanuts. Serve w/fish sauce & peanut sauce.

💸 ₫85,000 VND / $3.35 USD (Portion for 2)

🥢 *NEM CHUA*
(Fermented Pork Cake)
Pork thigh, pig skin, yellow sugar, salt, MSG, wine, honey, garlic, peppercorn, star gooseberry leaves, banana leaves. Cut meat into small pieces, remove fat. Grind then pound meat & garlic until thick. While pounding, add yellow sugar, salt, MSG, honey & wine. When thick enough, mix w/pig skin. Roll & shape by hand, put into the mold, cut into small cubes. Put peppercorn & garlic on top of the Nem Chua. 3 layer wrap: Star gooseberry leaves, cling film, banana leaves.

💸 ₫85,000 VND / $3.35 USD (Portion for 2)
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

*2. Cơm Niêu Đệ Nhất*
📍 2 Nguyễn Quý Đức, Khu đô thị An Phú An Khánh, Quận 2
📍 Số 6 Lương Khải Siêu, Bình Thọ, Thủ Đức
👩‍🍳 Ms. Uy (Owner)
﻿
🦐 *THỊT ĐÔNG w/PICKLED MUSTARD GREENS*
(Aspic/Meat Jelly)
Pork hock, pig skin, pork rib tips, pork ham hock, broth, wood ear mushroom, soy sauce, oyster sauce, ginger, fish sauce, pepper, caramel sauce, shallot, sugar, MSG, seasoning powder. Parboil all pork, rinse w/cold water, cut into pieces. Marinate w/ginger, pepper & sauces (caramel, fish, oyster, soy), shallot. Heat pan, add oil, ginger & shallot. Saute meat. Put in pot, add broth, simmer (3 hours). Add carrot (bottom), add mixture, top w/pepper. Refrigerate (2 hours) for jelly to set. Garnish w/coriander & aromatic leaves. Serve w/pickled mustard green.

💸 ₫95,000 VND / $3.74 USD
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

*3. Bình Điền Market - Mam Tom Stall*
📍 Đại lộ Nguyễn Văn Linh, Khu Phố 6, Quận 8
👩‍🍳 Ms Xuyen (Owner)

🦐 *BARREL OF MAM TOM*
Mam tom (shrimp paste), a staple of Vietnamese cuisine. Made by salt-fermenting crushed shrimp to a violet thick paste w/strong smell. Dipping sauce & spice.

💸 ₫30,000 VND / $1.18 USD (Per KG)
 - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

*4. Bún Đậu Tiến Hải*
📍 409 Đ. Nguyễn Tri Phương, Phường 5, Quận 10

🦀 *BÚN ĐẬU MẮM TÔM*
(Vermicelli w/Fried Tofu & Fermented Shrimp Paste)
Boiled pork trotter, fried tofu, crab cake made from ground crab & fat, spring rolls (freshwater shrimp, wood ear mushrooms, pork), pork ear sausage, blood sausage (pork meat, fat, coriander, scallions), cartilage sausage (meat, lemongrass, shallots), green sticky rice patties (meat, green rice), pork roll (meat, skin, perilla, fish mint, cucumber. Cut/fry.

💸 ₫109,000 VND / $4.30 USD (2 Pax)

🇰🇭 KEP-KAMPOT (Pepper Farm, Cambodia)

*1. Kep Crab Market*
📍 Krong Kaeb

🐟 *FISH PANCAKE*
Take out fish bones. Chop into a paste, add kroeung (spice mix), MSG, sugar. Smash till mixed. Shape into pancakes, deep fry for 3 mins.

💸 10,000KHR/$2.50
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

*2. $1 Chef’s Food Stall*
👨‍🍳 Chef Pi
﻿
🦐 *STIR FRIED TIGER PRAWNS*
Cut prawn face off, take out poop strand. Mix oil, garlic, green onion (chives) till fragrant. Put prawn in and lid on for 3 mins. Take lid off then stir. Add ground black pepper, special Kep sauce in, then mix. Sauce: MSG, sugar, chicken powder, chilly flakes, oyster sauce, sate sauce, milk, vinegar, palm sugar.

💸 51,437KHR/$12.50

🦪 *OYSTER*
Add crunchy powder, yellow food coloring, sugar, msg, chicken bullion, cream powder, and salt to water bugs. Squish to get the muddiness out and seasoning in. Deep fry for 5 mins.

💸 32,097KHR/$7.80 (12 Oysters) + 10,000KHR/$2.50 (cooking fee)
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

*3. La Plantation*
📍 Bosjheng Village, Krong Kampot
⏰ 9AM- 5PM
💁🏻‍♀️ Nathalie Chaboche

👨‍🌾 *FARM*
Has 20,000 vines, producing around 25 tonnes of pepper a year. Employs 300 people, half of which work for La Plantation full time. Fresh pepper is only good for 3 days after harvest, unless refrigerated, can extend to 10 days.
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

*4. Kep West*

🦀 *STIR-FRIED BLUE CRABS WITH GREEN PEPPER* 🟢
Cut and clean crabs. Flour crabs in a mixture of pepper, chicken powder, flour. Briefly deep fry bell pepper, onion, green pepper. Deep fry floured crabs for 2 mins. New pan, put in oil, deep fry veggie, special Kep West sauce, crab, basil, coconut milk. Sauce: cooking oil, fish sauce, dried shrimp, dried chili, coconut milk, coconut juice, garlic, chilly sauce, basil leaves.

🦀 *STIR-FRIED EGG BLUE CRABS WITH BLACK PEPPER SAUCE* ⚫
Same cooking, only sauce is different.

🇰🇭 BATTAMBANG (Cambodia)

*1. Brain Soup 502*
📍 Street 207, Krong Battambang, Cambodia
INTERVIEWEES: Liza

🧠 *BRAIN SOUP*:
Raw pig brain, pepper, secret vegetable broth. Steam for 5 minutes in a bowl. Add mushroom (the thin ones), steam for another 5 minutes. Finally add balut. Serve.

💸 10,000KHR/$2.50

🐸 *SUN DRIED FROG*
Marinate with fish & soy sauce, palm sugar, msg, salt, sugar, chili, garlic, ginger, dried bell peppers. Sun dry for 2 days. Deep fry.
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

*2. Frog Farm*
📍 Battambang, Cambodia
INTERVIEWEES: Som Han (Owner), ﻿Chea Chenda (Friend)
﻿
🐸 *STUFFED FROG*
Soak dry chili, soak dry glass noodles.Cut the feet off the frog and discard. Chop frog thighs off. Chop together with pork (bones and all). Mix with Kroeng. Drain and chop noodles mixture. Mix in roasted peanuts and the soaked chili. Add salt, sugar, chicken bullion, msg, chop to mix. Stuff frogs with mixture and grill for 30 minutes.

🐸 *FROG SOUP*
Add crunchy powder, yellow food coloring, sugar, msg, chicken bullion, cream powder, and salt to water bugs. Squish to get the muddiness out and seasoning in. Deep fry for 5 minutes.
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

*3. Rat Farm*
📍 Kampong Thom, NR62, Cambodia
INTERVIEWEE: Muy Chomrern

🐀 *GRILLED RAT*
Marination: pepper, shallots, garlic,smash together then add msg, chicken bullion, palm sugar, mix altogether, then rub on the rat. Add chinese black bean sauce and then oyster sauce. Rub on the rat. Split the bamboo stick to stick the rat between then tie with metal wire. Grill for roughly 1 hour.

🐀 *ROASTED RAT*
Marination: pepper, shallots, garlic,smash together then add msg, chicken bullion, palm sugar, mix altogether, then rub on the rat. Add chinese black bean sauce and then oyster sauce. Rub on the rat. Fold in the tail and put the marinated rat in a roasting cage. Hang the cage into a roasting vase for 1 hour.

🇰🇭 KAMPONG PHLUK (Cambodia)

*1. Local’s House*
📍 Kampong Phluk
INTERVIEWEES: Sang Kong (Village Chief) | ﻿Chhum Krern (Lady)

🐟 *PLEAR TREY CHAO*
(Raw River Fish Salad)
Slice fish, lime juice, chicken bullion, sugar, lemongrass, garlic, purple onion shallots, basil, msg, roasted peanuts, bean sprout, long bean, lemon juice and fish sauce. Mix it all together and then squish, drain the juice then add all the ingredients again, squish, plate.
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

*2. Floating Village*
📍 Kampong Phluk
INTERVIEWEES: ﻿Van (Wife) | Pherm (Husband)
﻿
☀️ *PRAHOK*
Debone Fish (Moonlight Gourami), wash the fish, salt the fish. Then dry the fish for one day and one night. Then, they smash it and put in jars. Age for at least 20 days, up to 3 years.

🍛 *PRAHOK ANG*
Chop pork, add prahok, chop together. Add lemongrass, Galangal, garlic, chilli, sugar, chicken bullion, msg, chopped until mixed. Wrap it in banana leaves and grill for 30 minutes. Then serve with raw vegetables: eggplant, cucumber, carrots, long bean, winged bean, round eggplant. Or cold rice.

🥗 *PRAHOK CHAO*
Chop prahok, lemongrass, garlic, chilli, sugar and then chop to mix. Add peanuts and chop more. Then add lime juice. Then serve with raw vegetables: eggplant, cucumber, carrots, long bean, winged bean, round eggplant. Or cold rice.

🐍 *GRILLED WATER SNAKES*
Kill the snakes by holding it by the tail and smash it on a log. Blanch the watersnakes in hot water, then remove the skin, put a stick through it. Make seasoning: palm sugar, salt, msg, chicken bullion, garlic and a shit ton of chili. Season the snake. Grill for 30 minutes.

🇰🇭 SKUN “SPIDER VILLAGE” & KAMPONG THOM (Cambodia)

*1. Vendor’s House*
📍 Skun, Cambodia
INTERVIEWEES: Liza

🐜 *RED TREE ANTS WITH BEEF*:
Fry garlic in Soy bean oil until golden brown, put in sliced beef, oyster sauce, msg, chicken bullion, sugar, let cook. Then put in red ants that have previously been soaked then drained. Mix until done.
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

*2. Bug Market*
📍 Skun, Cambodia
﻿
🦗 *CRICKETS*:
Crunchy powder (unbranded powder mix for frying), msg, chicken bullion, sugar, yellow food coloring, add all of this to the crickets, then cut up kaffir lime leaves. Mix, then deep fry for 5 minutes.

🪲 *GIANT WATER BUGS*:
Add the following ingredients to the water bugs: Crunchy powder, yellow food coloring, sugar, msg, chicken bullion, cream powder, salt. Then squish to get the muddiness out and seasoning in. Then deep fry for 5 minutes.

🪱 *SILKWORMS*:
Sik worm, msg, salt. Mix, then deep fry for 5 minutes.
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

*3. Hunting Grounds*
📍 Kampong Thom, NR62, Cambodia

🥣 *KROEUNG*
(Cambodian Spice mix):
Kafirr lime leaves, galangal, lemon grass, shallots, garlic, chilli, turmeric, fingerroot (wild ginger), wild galangal. Mix it, then smash it with a mortar and pestle (stick). Done.
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

*4. Wholesaler’s house*
📍 Skun, Cambodia
INTERVIEWEES: Soy Lon

🕷️ *FRIED TARANTULA*:
Crunchy powder, cream powder, msg, chicken bullion, red food coloring, sugar, then mix with tarantula then deep fry for 5 minutes.

🍲 *CRICKET SOUP*:
First put prahok (fermented fish paste), then cricket in a pot with water. Then mushrooms, cucumbers, peppers. Then season with Kroeung (special type with smashed roasted rice in it), msg, sugar, salt (a bit too much apparently). Then boil for 15 minutes. Then top it off with Plie, Anong, Maom, Saom (all of which are local herbs).

🇰🇭 PHNOM PENH (Cambodia)

*1. Mimi Brain Soup*
📍 Calmette St. 53, Phnom Penh 55555 Cambodia (Central Market)
OPEN: 6am-4pm

🧠 *NHOM BANH JOK KOUR KDAM*
(Crab Brain Soup):
Add pork blood jelly, tofu, pork intestine, unlaid chicken eggs, meatball, squid, Cambodian ‘pate’, and crab brain to pork bone soup. The ‘crab brain’ is made by blending meat of river crab, taking juice out, then steam.
💸 10,000KHR/$2.50
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

*2. Lim Koucha Wonton*
📍 Central Market
OPEN: 6am-11am
﻿
🍜 *KUY TEAV*
(Dry Rice Noodle Dish):
Blanch bean sprouts, rice noodles, shrimp, bok choy, wonton, ground pork, pork fat in a pork broth then blanch the noodles in water.
💸 10,000KHR/$2.50
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

*3. E Srey*
📍 Central Market
OPEN: 10am-4pm

🥣 *BORBOR PHEK*
(Phek Porridge):
Add bean sprouts, banana flower, compluk/water hyacith (purple flower), Pka snao/soponge flower (yellow flower), konthom thet/white lead tree (vegetable), water lily (cylindrical part) to rice porridge, kroeng (spice mix), garlic and taro stem. Top with snails.
💸 10,000KHR/$2.50
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

*4. Majas Srok*
📍 រាជធានី, Street 51, 154 Dekcho Damdin St. (154), Phnom Penh 120202, Cambodia
OPEN: 6am-9pm

🐟 *AMOK*
(Fish Curry):
Fold banana leaves into bowl. Mix eggs, Kroeng (lemongrass, garlic, shallots, tumeric, wild ginger, galangal, kafirr lime leaves, coconut milk, water), sugar, chicken bullion powder, fish sauce, coconut milk, fish. Put amok leaf into bottom of banana leaf bowl. Put mixture into leaf bowl. Steam for 20 min.
💸 20,000KHR/$5.00
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

*5. Malis Restaurant*
📍 Phnom, 136 Norodom Blvd, Penh 12301, Cambodia
OPEN: 6:30am-10:30am

🍲 *SAMLOR KORKO*
(Soup made with Prahok):
Brown the pork ribs in oil, add kroeng (spice mix), fish sauce, prahok, palm sugar. Add ‘veggies’ (long beans, pumpkin, jackfruit, papaya). Add fish broth. Cook for 20 min. Add fish and coconut milk. Add leaf vegetables (Moringa).
💸 45,000KHR/$11.00

🇵🇭 TINGLAYAN, BUSCALAN, KALINGA (Philippines)

*1. D'Farm*
INTERVIEWEES: ﻿Lorena (translator) | Aldrin (tour guide and chef, host family) | Ken (chef)

🐔 *PINAKBET*
(Stir-fried Chicken with Veggies):
In a pan, heat oil. Add Garlic, Tomatoes. Add Chicken. Add Salt and Pepper. Add shredded Squash, then cover for about 30 seconds. Uncover and add String Beans, Jungle Bitter Gourd. Cover, uncover. Add Okra, Eggplant, and Chili.
﻿
🐟 *TILAPIA*
(Deep-fried Local Fish):
Marinate in Salt, Pepper, and Vinegar for 3 hours. Deep-fry until crispy.
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

*2. Host family's home)*
INTERVIEWEES: ﻿﻿Lorena (translator) | Aldrin (host family, helping with butchering)

🛖 *TINGLAYAN VILLAGE*
Small, remote village that sits at the mountain side of Buscalan in Kalinga. Home of the living legend and an indigenous tattoo artist, Maria Oggay AKA Apo Whang Od.

🪶 *BUTBUT*
(Indigenous Tribe):
Their natural climate solutions were embedded in these farming practices. Primarily thrive on rice agriculture and recently on tourism by providing guide services, translations and home accommodations.

🪓 *PIG SLAUGHTERING RITUAL*
(Generational Tradition)
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

*3. Tinglayan Village*
INTERVIEWEES: Lorena (translator) | Chui (fixer)

🍖 *ETAG*
(Rotten Meat):
Sprinkle Salt. Cure for ﻿about a week. Sun dry for several weeks or months. Also hanged when it rains. Boil for about 1 hour before eating.
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -

*4. Tinglayan Village, Buscalan*
INTERVIEWEES: ﻿﻿Maria Oggay “Apo Whang Od” (tattoo lady)

🍲 *DNUGUAN*
(Pork Blood & Intestine Soup):
Clean Pig organs thoroughly. In a pot, boil innards for 25 minutes. Chop into bite-sized pieces. Peel and grate Papaya. Stir fry onion and garlic, then add Ginger. Add organs, then cover for 5 minutes. Add salt, papaya. Cover. Add Blood (mixed with Vinegar). Mix, then add ground Chili.

🐷 *WATWAT*
(Boiled Pork):
Boil in salted water for about 1 hour.

🇵🇭 MAYOYAO, IFUGAO (Philippines)

*1. Lynda's Eatery*
INTERVIEWEES: ﻿Detchie (Co-Host) | Ate Lynda (Owner)

🐌 *GINGA*
(Soft-Shelled Snails Stew):
Boil GINGA. Sauté aromatics. Add snails and stir-fry. Close lid. Add salt & pepper to taste.﻿

🦗 *KHACHIW with CHAJAP*
(Fish Soup with River Crickets):
Boil KHACHIW (Fish) and CHAJAP (Cricket). ﻿Sauté aromatics. Mix them together.
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -  

*2. Mayoyao Japanese Eel Hatchery*

🇯🇵 *PIKAW*
(Japanese Eel):
The Japanese Weather Loach (PIKAW), was introduced by the Japanese in the Philippines during WW II. In Cordillera, it was historically abundant in rice paddies, however due to commercialization the reproduction of the PIKAW depleted.
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -  

*3. Local Cafe*
INTERVIEWEES: Fidel (Eel Hatcher)

🪱 *PIKAW*
(Japanese Eel Stew):
Sauté aromatics with some Liquid Seasoning. Stir-fry with PIKAW. Add coconut milk and water. let simmer for about 10-15 mins. Add String Beans, Fish Paste, Onion, Green Chili.﻿﻿


🔥 *DEEP FRIED PIKAW*
Deep-fry PIKAW in Oil in 10-15 mins, or until golden brown and crispy enough. Salt and Pepper. Serve with sauce made from Vinegar and Burned Garlic.
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -  

*4. Bongan Rice Terrace*
INTERVIEWEES: ﻿﻿Fidel (Snail Forager, Man in White Tee) | Eduardo ﻿(Main Chef at Cow's Location) | Detchie (Co-Host Woman) | Chui (Cameo Actor)

🏏 *LATEG TI BAKA / SOUP NUMBER 5*
(Beef Bats and Balls): 
Boil cow penis and balls for 30 mins, then drain. Sauté aromatics. Add water. Add penis and balls back to the pot, then more water. Salt to taste. Close lid, and boil for another 45 mins - 1 hour.

🍲 *PAPAITAN*
(Cow Bitter Soup):
Clean organs thoroughly then boil.﻿ Remove from pot and chop into smaller pieces. Sieve juice from stomach into bucket. Sauteé aromatics. Remove some Ginger and use for the penis soup. Add the organs back to soup. Add a little bile and sieved stomach juice to the pot. Add salt to taste and green chili.

🐮 *SUNGO*
(Cow Nose Soup):
﻿Remove head and preserve its entirety. Boil water & add salt.
Put head in & boil for 2 hours.

🇵🇭 SUBIC BAY (Philippines)

1. Kanawan Aeta Community Village
INTERVIEWEES: ﻿Samuel Balintay (Sam) | Dandye (Hunter) | Ate Rosario (Woman in Pink)

🍠 BIGA
(Boiled or Roasted Taro):
Boil in hot pot of water / Throw on fire. Served, peeled at table.

🔥 SINILAB 
(Woodfire-Roasted Chicken):
﻿Throw entire Chicken into fire and roast. Remove from fire to scrape off charcoal and pluck feathers. Once it’s clean, remove internal organs and fill chicken with TANGLAD leaves and lemongrass. Tie chicken's legs together and rub the outside with salt. Skewer the chicken and roast over fire for 30 more minutes. Serve.

🍲 SINIGANG
(Chicken Sour Soup):
﻿Make SINILAB (Fire-roasted Chicken). Chop Sinilab into small pieces and stuff into a bamboo tube. Add Salt, BILOKAW (Local Sour Leaves, which act as jungle vinegar) and water. Close top of tube with banana leaves and rest against a fire to cook. Drain soup into separate containers for drinking and remove solid contents of the bamboo tube to eat separately. Serve.﻿
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -  

2. Bat Cave ⛰
ADDRESS: Subic Bay
INTERVIEWEES: ﻿Samuel Balintay (Sam) | Dandye (Local Hunter)

🎯 BAT HUNTING
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -  

3. Kanawan Aeta Community Village
INTERVIEWEES: Sam (Co-Host) | Dandye (Hunter) | Mary

🦎 LIZARD ADOBO 
Made from BAYAWAK (local term for Monitor Lizard). The lizard is thrown into fire so its skin can be scraped clean. After washing with water, it’s chopped into small pieces. In a pan fry Garlic, Onion, and Meat. Stir until meat browns. Next, add Soy Sauce, Vinegar and cook for about 20 minutes. *Sour leaves and salt may also be ingredients*
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -  

4. Kanawan Aeta Community Village
INTERVIEWEES: Sam (Co-Host) | Dandye (Hunter) | Carl Chuidian (Chui)

🐒 MONKEY "CEVICHE" 
(Vinegar Stir-fried Monkey):
Add cleaned Monkey Skin, Chopped Shallots, and Chopped Ginger to a pan. Sauté. Add Vinegar, Salt, and Oil. Fry for a few minutes and serve.

🍖 GRILLED MONKEY
﻿Chop the Monkey into medium sized pieces and rub down with Salt. Cook over fire. Serve.

🦇 BAT WING SOUP
﻿Throw entire bat onto grill. Chop bats wings off. Boil in pot with Sour Leaves, Lemongrass, KAMIAS (cucumber tree), and Salt. Serve.

2. Loida’s
ADDRESS: Tondo, Manila
INTERVIEWEES: Chef Tatung (co-host) Ate Loida

♻️ MONOK (RECYCLED HOTEL MEAT):
The assortment of Beef, Pork, and Chicken Meat is transferred to a pan where it is shredded by hand. Vinegar, Soy Sauce, Onion, and Chili Peppers are added to the pan and the meat is boiled for 5-10 minutes. Drain the meat. In a pan, fry together: Oil, Garlic, Onion, and Chili Peppers. Next, add the boiled meat back into the pan and season with Salt, Pepper and Oyster Sauce. After mixing, let the meat sit untouched in the pan for 15-20 min until the bottom has a crunchy crust. Serve.
💸 PRICE: 20 PHP / $0.36 USD per portion
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -  
3. Ate Evelyn’s
ADDRESS: Happy Land, Tondo, Manila
INTERVIEWEES: Chui (co-host) Chef Tatung (co-host) Ate Evelyn

🗑️ PAGPAG
(Recycled Fast Food Meat):
The sorted meat is washed with water, then boiled, then drained. For the marination: Onion, Garlic, Soy Sauce, Sprite, MSG, Pineapple Juice is mixed with the meat. It is then fried in hot oil for 5 min. Serve. (Fried Type) 
Meat is sorted, then washed with water, then boiled, then drained. Sautee Oil, Garlic, and the meat. Next, mix in: Sugar, Pineapple Juice, Soy Sauce, Vinegar, MSG, and Sprite. Mix and let cook for a few minutes. Add in Smashed Crackers/Biscuits and Milk Powder. Cook for a few more minutes. Serve.﻿ (Adobo Type) 
💸 PRICE: 30 PHP / $0.54 USD per portion

1. Tuỳ Tâm Vegan
ADDRESS: 176 Ngô Gia Tự Street, Ward 9, D10, HCMC
OPERATION HOURS: 11am - 2pm, Mon - Fri
INTERVIEWEES: Calvin (co-host) Long (vendor lady)

🥗 VEGAN PORK AND SPRING ROLLS NOODLE SALAD
(Bún Bì Thịt Nướng Chả Giò Chay) - aka Vegan Bún Thịt Nướng:
All ingredients in the bowl include: Bún (noodles), Green vegetables such as rau quế (basil), lettuce, bean sprouts, shredded cucumber, Vegan grilled pork, Vegan spring rolls, Vegan pork rinds, Pickles, Scallion confit, Peanuts, Chili pepper, and Vegan fish sauce.

💸 PRICE: 5,000 VND / $0.20 USD per bowl
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -  
2. Bánh Canh Cua Phạm Văn Chí
ADDRESS: 360 Phạm Văn Chí Street, D6
OPERATION HOURS: 3:30pm - 8pm
INTERVIEWEES: Calvin (co-host) Loan (vendor lady)

🍜 RIP-OFF” CRAB TAPIOCA NOODLE 
(Bánh Canh Cua “Chặt Chém"):
Before adding to the bowl, dip bánh canh (tapioca noodle) into the broth. Toppings - crab claws, shredded crab meat, pig trotter, sliced pork - are also dipped in the broth for 30 seconds, then added to the bowl. Add blood pudding and fried dough to the bowl. Top with some chopped cilantro and scallions.

💸💸 PRICE: 350,000 VND / $14.24 USD per bowl
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -  
3. Oriental Pearl, Landmark 81 Building
ADDRESS: Floor 66, Landmark 81 Building - 720A Đ. Điện Biên Phủ Street, Vinhomes Tân Cảng, Bình Thạnh
OPERATION HOURS: 6am - 9pm
INTERVIEWEES: Calvin (co-host) Lê Trung (chef)

⚜️ PHO KING
(Special dish for their “Month of Pho”):
In the kitchen, add ingredients to a bowl: Phở noodle, short ribs, herbs. Then, more ingredients are assembled when at the table. Place gold leaves on the inside, close to the lip of the bowl. Add Foie gras. Weigh Truffle on the scale, then slice into the bowl. Pour the hot broth and finally, add ground pepper


💸💸💸 PRICE: 4,000,000 VND / $164 USD per portion

🇺🇸 MIAMI (MIA aka The Magic City)

1. PROCESSING FACILITY/FISH HOUSE
ADDRESS: 1264 Ocean View Ave, Marathon, FL 33050

🦞 STEAMED LOBSTER:
Steam 400 lbs of lobster for roughly 20 minutes. Take the green stone crab and grade them (we did red because we didn’t have green). Place them in bags and stick in the steamer to cook for 9 min, then stick in the ice bath for about 6 min. Then bag them and pack in the cooler and then exteriors.
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -  
2. BILLY’S STONE CRABS
ADDRESS: 400 N Ocean Dr, Hollywood, FL 33019
INTERVIEWEES: Michael Hershey (GM) Guga Foods + Carlos Bassat (Chef)

🦐 SEAFOOD TOWER:
Ingredients include; Florida Stone Crab, King Crab, Jumbo Shrimp, Oysters, Florida Lobster tails, and Jumbo lump crab meat.

🦀 KEY WEST GROUPER:
﻿Lightly sautéed in a hot pan. Season with salt and pepper. Deglaze with white wine. Add Butter, and thyme. Finish in the oven for about 15 minutes. Plating consists of; Jumbo Lump crab meat, Grouper, Jumbo Shrimp, Avocado, Beurre Blanc (white wine lemon butter), Topped with greens.
💸 PRICE: $50.00

🇺🇸SOUTH CAROLINA

1. MR ATKINS’ BOAT
ADDRESS: Eddings Point Boat Landing
INTERVIEWEE: Ed Atkins + Tendaji

🇺🇸SHRIMP AND GRITS: Cook shrimp in a skillet with fat. Remove shrimp, add onion, salt, and roux (oil and rice flour browned down). Add water and mix. For grits, combine water, heirloom grits, salt, and butter. Cook for about 1 hr. To serve, place grits on a plate and top with shrimp roux.
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -  
2. GULLAH EXPRESS
ADDRESS: Melody Ln, South Carolina 29920, USA
INTERVIEWEE: Sherry Johnson - Owner

🇺🇸FRIED SHARK: Place the shark in flour and fry. 
💸PRICE: $16.00

🇺🇸SHRIMP AND CRAB BURGER: Blend shrimp and crab in a blender. Add seasoning, blend, and adjust to taste. Form into a patty, lightly coat in flour (no egg wash), and fry. Place on a bun and serve with special sauce.
💸PRICE: $17.00
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -  
2. PENN CENTER
ADDRESS: 16 Penn Center Cir E, St Helena Island, SC 29920, United States

🇺🇸FROGMORE STEW (LOWCOUNTRY BOIL): In a large pot, add water and season with Garlic Powder, Old Bay Seasoning, Salt, Hot Crab Seasoning, and Garlic Seasoning. Include onion and chilies. Cut potatoes into large chunks. Once boiling, add corn and cook until just beginning to get tender. Add potatoes, and cook until fully tender. Introduce sausage, stir, and let it cook. Finally, add shrimp and cook until pink and opaque. Once cooked, carefully place everything on a large foil tray.

🇺🇸OKRA SOUP WITH OXTAIL AND SHRIMP: In a pot, bring broth to a boil. Stir in cooked ox tail. Add various beans, stir, and cook until boiling, stirring occasionally. Chop okra and add it to the pot, stirring well. Continue stirring until the broth thickens. Pour more water and let it simmer. Finally, add shrimp and cook until they turn pink.

- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -  
2. JACOB KNOWLES' BOAT
ADDRESS: Winter Harbor
INTERVIEWEE: Jacob Knowles
YOUTUBE: https://www.youtube.com/@jacobknowles5421 

🦞STEAMED LOBSTER: Steam lobsters for about 12-15 minutes, depending on size. Melt butter and then add vinegar.
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -  
3. PORTLAND LOBSTER COMPANY
ADDRESS: 180 Commercial St, Portland, ME, United States
OPERATION HOURS: 11:00AM to 10:00PM seven days a week for the summer
INTERVIEWEES:  Ethan Morgan (Owner) + Carissa Fifield (General Manager) 

🇺🇸NEW ENGLAND CLAM CHOWDER: Melt salted butter in a pot and stir in chopped pork until it turns golden brown. Add chopped onion and celery, gently stirring. Introduce anchovy fillet and chopped garlic, and more salted butter. Gradually add all-purpose flour, stirring continuously until the mixture thickens. Incorporate chopped clams and pour clam juice into the pot, stirring well. Add cooked diced potatoes and stir, then season with salt, white pepper, dried parsley, and basil, ensuring even distribution. Finally, pour in Half and Half, continuing to stir. Serve the dish with diced green onions. 

💸PRICE: $8.99 

🦞LOBSTER ROLL: Hold the tail and gently squeeze to detach it from the head. Remove the lobster meat from the tail shells. Break the claws and extract the meat, then chop it into bite-sized pieces. Assemble the lobster rolls by placing a lettuce leaf inside the bun, creating a bed for the lobster meat, and filling the buns with the chopped lobster. Serve the lobster rolls with fries and lime, topping each roll with melted butter.

💸PRICE: $25.00

🇵🇷MORCILLA: Clean the intestines. Separately, blend all of the veggies. Blend the blood to make it smooth. Cook rice. Stuff the intestines with the entire mixture. 
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -  
2. HOME OF DONA MARIA 
INTERVIEWEE: ﻿﻿Maria 

🇵🇷GANDINGA (PORK STEW): Chop the organs finely (liver, lungs and heart). Chop pork meat, then add sofrito (puerto rican salsa), olives, seasoning and hot peppers and potatoes. Add to a pot and boil for 45 minutes. 

🇵🇷 PATITAS DE CERDO CON GARBANZOS (PIG FEET STEW): In a pot, boil chickpeas and pig feet. Add grated plantains, squash and seasonings (cilantro and achiote). 
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -  
3. LA RUMBA BAR & RESTAURANT 
ADDRESS: Yabucoa 00767, Puerto Rico

🇵🇷PASTELILLOS DE CONEJO (RABBIT MEAT PIES) 
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -  
4. HOME OF DONA MARIA 
🇵🇷PASTELES: Peel potatoes, malanga, plantain and green bananas (young plantain). Grate everything and combine. Cut the plantain leaves for wrapping. Add filling on leaves and wrap. 

🇵🇷LECHON

- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -  
1. LA VERGÜENZA
ADDRESS: 280 Calle Norzagaray, San Juan, 00901
INTERVIEWEE: Chef Edgar or ﻿Chef Anthony Báez

🇵🇷CHULETA CAN CAN (CAN CAN CUTLET, FRIED PORK CHOP): Prepare a delectable pork chop by boiling the meat until tender. Then, deep fry it for approximately 15 minutes until golden and crispy. Serve this savory delight on a plate alongside arroz con gandules and deliciously fried plantains for a flavorful and satisfying meal. 
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -  
2. KIOSCO EL BORICUA
ADDRESS: PR-187, Carolina, Loíza 00772
INTERVIEWEE: ﻿﻿Zereida Rodríguez

🇵🇷PIONONOS (FILLED PLANTAIN): Use ripe plantains to create cylinders by wrapping long slices around a savory beef filling. Once assembled, coat these delicious parcels in a batter made from flour and egg before frying them to a golden crisp.

🇵🇷ALCAPURRIA (STUFFED FRITTER/ PUERTO RICAN FRITTER): Prepare dough using a blend of plantains, achiote oil, and seasoning, and shape it into squares. Fill these squares with a mixture of fresh crab and seal them closed. Fry these parcels until golden and crispy. Serve these delectable crab-filled treats alongside Pique, a zesty Puerto Rican-style hot sauce. 
- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -  
PUERTA DEL MAR
ADDRESS: Caretera 187 k.m 4.4, Loíza, 00772
INTERVIEWEE: Tibizay Almanzar

🇵🇷CHICKEN PINCHOS (SKEWERED MEAT): Marinate fresh chicken thighs in a blend of fresh garlic, white vinegar, sazon, adobo criollo, and achiote (annatto). Skewer the marinated chicken and grill it for approximately 5-10 minutes, generously brush homemade BBQ sauce onto the chicken while it cooks. Serve with garlic bread and an extra drizzle of BBQ sauce. 


- - - - - - - - - - - - - - - - -  
EL RANCHO DE DON NANDO
ADDRESS: PR-809 k.m. 3.2 Bo, Naranjito, 00719
INTERVIEWEE: Hector Lopez

🇵🇷LONGANIZA (SPICED PORK SAUSAGE): Grind pork, season with adobo mix and secret ingredients. Stuff seasoned meat into casings, then hang over homemade smoker for smoking. Fry before serving.

🇵🇷SMOKED PORK: Season the pork generously with your preferred seasonings, then hang it to smoke. Prior to serving, give it a quick fry for added flavor and texture.

🇵🇷PUERTO RICO: Puerto Rico is a Caribbean island and an unincorporated territory of the United States. It has a population of around 3.2 million people. Its cuisine is a vibrant mix of Spanish, African, Taíno, and American influences. Dishes like mofongo (mashed plantains), arroz con gandules (rice with pigeon peas), and lechón asado (roast pork) are staples reflecting this fusion. Join us on the #BestEverPuertoRicoTour as we taste our way across the island!

videos.title: How Do We Play with Talking Tom? Feeding Him, Brushing Teeth, and Surprises!
videos.description:
Hi, friends! 😊 Today we have a super fun video, and me and Eva invite you to join us in our world of games and adventures! It all starts when I wake up because my dad woke me up (as usual! 😜), and I immediately start playing a game with my friend — Talking Tom! 🐱 This is such a fun game, and you won’t believe what happens next!

First, I feed Tom, and then my parents decide to feed me, just like in a real family! 🍽️ But then it’s time for something really important — we all brush our teeth! 🦷 Who brushes better: Tom or me? I repeat everything Tom does, and it’s so funny! Eva also joins in and teaches Tom how to brush teeth properly! By the way, how do you brush your teeth? Eva and I try to be careful because it’s important for our teeth!

After brushing our teeth, we have a yummy breakfast of porridge, and Eva and I eat together! 🥣 Then it’s time to dry our hair, and we both dry our hair while copying Tom’s moves! But suddenly… we decide maybe we should take a bath under a real water shower, just like in the game with Tom! And guess what? At the end, Tom turns into a real fluffy cat! 🐾

Now we don’t just play with him, we have a real fluffy friend to play with, feed, and have fun together! It was amazing! 💖 Watch the video to see how it all happened and make sure to give us a thumbs up if you love Talking Tom and his friends too! 😊 Don’t forget to subscribe to our channel so you don’t miss any new adventures!

videos.title: Alyssa’s Magical Slime & Play-Doh Pranks: Fun DIY Adventures with Dad! Cool Off, Snack & Laugh
videos.description:
Welcome to Alyssa’s Magical Slime World — a place full of fun, creativity, and endless laughs! 🌟 In this exciting episode, you’ll see how Alyssa, the most playful and creative girl, finds clever ways to help her dad with everyday problems using slime, Play-Doh, and her boundless imagination. 😄

The story begins on a sunny day when Alyssa’s dad is relaxing on his hammock in the yard. 🏖️ The sun is shining brightly, and it’s getting hotter by the minute! Dad is feeling the heat, and he’s in need of some serious cooling down. He calls out to his trusty little helper, Alyssa, to save the day! But instead of just bringing a regular ice pack or some cold water, Alyssa has something much more fun and magical up her sleeve. 💡

Alyssa rushes off to her secret laboratory (aka her playroom!) and decides to make something super cool — ice slime! ❄️🧊 With a dash of glitter and a swirl of magical colors, Alyssa creates a slime masterpiece that looks just like ice! She mixes and stretches the slime until it’s perfect and brings it back to her dad. But instead of handing him the ice, she gently places it on his face — and the funniest thing happens! 😂 Dad’s surprised face says it all! The icy slime helps him cool off, but it’s also squishy, stretchy, and so much fun to play with. Alyssa giggles as her dad’s face melts into a smile. Mission accomplished! 🥳

Just when dad thinks the surprises are over, his stomach growls. Now he’s hungry! 🍔 Dad asks Alyssa if she can help him find something to eat. Being the clever girl she is, Alyssa decides it’s time for her next prank! She rushes to her collection of Play-Doh toys and makes a plate of delicious-looking French fries. 🍟 They look just like the real thing! When Alyssa proudly presents the fries to her dad, he’s so impressed. He takes a big bite… but something’s not quite right! 😲 The fries are made of Play-Doh! Alyssa bursts into laughter as dad realizes he’s been tricked again. What a funny and creative way to play with food!

But the fun doesn’t stop there. After the French fry prank, dad starts craving something sweet. 🍰 He asks Alyssa if she can make him a tasty dessert. Of course, Alyssa has another trick up her sleeve! She runs off to make a toy cupcake. 🎂 This cupcake looks extra yummy, with colorful sprinkles and whipped cream on top. Alyssa brings the cupcake to her dad, and just as he’s about to take a bite… surprise! The cupcake is filled with slime! 💦 Slime oozes out everywhere, and dad can’t believe his eyes! Alyssa’s pranks keep getting better and better. She’s full of surprises, and dad is always up for the fun!

Now it’s time for the grand finale. Alyssa, being the ultimate prankster, has one last surprise for her dad. She brings out a giant watermelon 🍉 — but this is no ordinary watermelon. Hidden inside is more of Alyssa’s magical slime! When dad tries to slice the watermelon, out comes the gooey, stretchy slime! Dad’s shocked but can’t stop laughing. Even though he’s been pranked all day, he’s having the best time playing with Alyssa. Their bond is full of love, laughter, and endless creativity.

At the end of the day, what makes this video special is the love and joy between Alyssa and her dad. It shows how parents can engage with their kids, create wonderful memories, and have a blast together. 💕 From cooling off with icy slime to hilarious food pranks, every moment is filled with laughter and excitement. If you want to see how slime, Play-Doh, and a little bit of creativity can turn a normal day into an extraordinary adventure, you’ve come to the right place!

Join Alyssa and her dad in this magical, playful journey and discover how easy it is to bring joy and laughter to your family. Alyssa’s creativity and sense of humor will inspire you to try your own fun pranks and DIY projects at home. Make sure to watch till the end to see all the surprising and funny moments! videos.title: 60 Minutes educational video for children from Alice and Dad. Hide-and-seek, counting, shapes
videos.description:
60 minutes of fun and educational activities for kids! 🌟 This one-hour video is specially designed for children aged 2 to 5, offering a perfect combination of play and learning. Dad and his daughter will guide your little ones through a series of educational games that will help them learn colors, numbers, counting, and so much more! 🎨🔢 This video is ideal for family viewing and guarantees an hour of entertainment for everyone who watches.

Throughout the full hour, children will watch as Alice and her dad play various games, teaching toddlers counting and introducing them to important concepts needed for school readiness. Alice learns to count, names colors, and identifies objects and shapes while playing with her favorite toys. Meanwhile, she enjoys the playful interaction with her dad, and her joyful emotions will captivate young viewers!

---

**Here’s what your child will experience:**

1. **Learning colors**: Your child will be introduced to basic colors through fun and interactive games. Watch as Alice identifies red, blue, green, yellow, and more! These activities not only teach children colors but also help develop visual and cognitive skills by associating colors with objects.

2. **Counting from 1 to 10**: Alice and her dad make counting fun! Through play, Alice learns to count her toys, swimming pool items, and even her favorite cars. She counts up to ten and then practices reverse counting from 100, making sure children understand numbers both ways. This activity will help preschoolers develop an early understanding of math and prepare them for school.

3. **Hide and seek with toys**: In one of the games, Alice plays hide-and-seek with her dolls, cars, and other toys. She searches for them all over the room, counting each one as she finds it. Hide and seek is an exciting and engaging game that helps children improve problem-solving skills, memory, and coordination.

4. **Swimming pool fun**: Alice jumps into the pool to retrieve her toys, counting them one by one. This simple but fun game introduces the concept of counting while also demonstrating motor skills and coordination. Alice's excitement as she collects each toy keeps kids engaged, and her laughter makes the experience even more joyful.

5. **Learning to eat**: One part of the video focuses on teaching children healthy eating habits. Alice and her dad sit down to eat together, and she learns not to be afraid of trying new foods. They discuss the benefits of vegetables, fruits, and other healthy foods in a playful manner, encouraging children to eat well and develop good habits early on.

6. **Songs for kids**: What’s an educational video without some music? Throughout the video, you’ll hear fun, catchy songs that children can sing along to. These songs are designed to make learning numbers and letters enjoyable. Children will love singing along with Alice as they learn new things through music!

7. **Interactive play**: The entire video is filled with interactive moments where kids can follow along. Whether it’s counting toys, learning colors, or joining in a fun song, children are encouraged to actively participate rather than just watch. This involvement enhances the learning experience and helps kids retain what they’ve learned.

---

**Why you and your kids will love this video:**

- It’s **1-hour long**, perfect for parents looking for a lengthy, uninterrupted educational activity.
- **Designed for children ages 2-5**, it’s the perfect mix of fun and education.
- It teaches **counting, colors, and shapes** in a playful manner.
- This video is ideal for preparing children for **preschool and kindergarten**, introducing early concepts like numbers, colors, and social play.
- The activities in this video promote **motor skill development**, such as swimming, sorting toys, and playing hide-and-seek.
- It includes **playful games**, which encourage active engagement, not just passive watching, allowing kids to participate in the learning process.
- **Catchy songs** make learning more enjoyable, combining music and education to keep kids entertained while they learn.

This description ensures that your video targets the right audience looking for **long-form educational content** for children. It focuses on key learning activities, while also emphasizing the fun and engaging elements that will keep kids entertained for the entire 60 minutes.

videos.title: Food challenge: Dad and Alice try toy food and go fishing for chocolate fish. Alice jokes with dad
videos.description:
Welcome to our family channel, where fun and learning for kids go hand in hand! 🌟 Each of our videos is an opportunity to explore a new world filled with unexpected adventures and valuable life lessons. In today’s video, Dad and his energetic daughter Alice embark on a fun culinary adventure that begins with play and ends with laughter and joy! 🎉

Like many kids, Alice loves to use her imagination and play with toy food. Instead of real cooking, she offers her dad imaginary dishes, sparking a playful adventure full of giggles. Dad, always ready to support his daughter, eagerly dives into her world, where anything can be part of a delightful cooking show. The two share not just food but a fun and memorable experience that strengthens their bond and fills their home with joy.

👨‍👧 In this video, you’ll see:

How Alice uses her creativity to offer her dad imaginative solutions, developing her problem-solving skills and learning through play.
A dad who supports his daughter in every way, showing the importance of patience, attention, and love in raising children.
Many funny and touching moments that will remind everyone how important it is to spend time with loved ones, joining in their games and fantasies.
This video is perfect for parents and kids alike because it shows how you can learn and have fun at the same time. Through play, Alice is learning important life skills—she’s developing her language, motor skills, and imagination. While she’s having fun with pretend food, she’s also picking up concepts of cooking and collaboration in her own unique way. And her dad shows us all how crucial it is to be part of a child’s world, supporting their interests and helping them explore new aspects of life.

🔍 Lessons kids can learn from this video:

The importance of creativity and imagination. Through play, children learn how to solve problems, invent new ideas, and turn them into reality. Alice, creating her own “cooking show,” demonstrates that imagination is an essential part of any learning process. She turns everyday objects into something extraordinary.
The value of family and interaction. Dad and Alice demonstrate how shared play and spending time with loved ones can strengthen family bonds. This teaches us the importance of listening to each other, being patient, and showing respect. Family time, no matter how simple, becomes precious.
Learning through play. Many skills, like concentration, coordination, and communication, can be developed through simple games. Alice is not only learning to have fun but also engaging with her dad, making the learning process both enjoyable and meaningful.
Besides their fun with toy food, this episode also highlights another important value—spending quality time together. As we all know, the most memorable moments in life aren’t always the big celebrations or vacations, but rather the times we spend laughing, playing, and learning together with the people we love. Simple moments of connection, like the ones shared in this video, can lead to the strongest memories and the best life lessons.

👨‍👧 Heartwarming moments:

One of the funniest moments in the video is when Dad tries to lie down and rest after all the excitement, but Alice, with her playful energy, quickly steals the pillow from under his head! This scene will make anyone who has ever played with small children smile, as it perfectly captures the unpredictability and joy they bring into our lives.
Another hilarious scene unfolds when Dad catches a chocolate fish in the pool. But Alice, always full of surprises, finds a dried fish from her cat’s bowl and suggests a trade. This moment is full of laughter, as Dad has to decide whether to stick with the chocolate fish or go for the real one!
But what’s most important is that in every video, we don’t just play—we also aim to share essential values like love, mutual respect, cooperation, and the joy of learning something new. Children learn not just through books and lessons but through the daily moments they share with their families. This video is all about those everyday moments that shape us and teach us the most valuable lessons in life.

🎯 What we teach on our channel:

Imagination without limits. We show kids that they can invent many amazing stories and games using the simple things around them. Even toy food or a poolside game can turn into an exciting adventure! We encourage creativity and problem-solving in a fun, lighthearted way.
Family values. We always emphasize the importance of family. Support, love, and spending time together are what bring us closer and help each family member feel important and valued. Family time is about making memories, building trust, and fostering lifelong bonds.

Twitter & Instagram @NetNobody 

Below are the talented People I love and live with, we've gone through a lot together so get to know them! 

Chadd (Unwoji) http://www.twitch.tv/chuddnelius (Producer)

Michael (Red) http://www.youtube.com/user/redvacktor (Vlogger/Gamer)

Jason (Foxy) http://www.youtube.com/foxycomedy

Breanna (Breezy) (She just started creating content!)
http://https://www.youtube.com/channel/UC86G98xJXLaFuobAkwdG1Uw

If you've made it through to the end of the description, I'd like to thank you for going out of your way to follow me on everything, and joining me on this next journey.

Life has been really hard for me mentally, growing up was really hard and life has thrown me a lot of curveballs, but I geniunely want to say thank you so much, to my second family, all of you out here, in the void that is the internet. When I was growing up, dealing with the craziness at home, the internet is where I went to truly be me and express myself. I'm sorry I abandoned those who lifted me up in the first place, and I'm sorry I lost myself, thank you for lifting me again now, even when I was in my darkest moments of my life, I'll continue to try to better myself, and become someone I'm proud of, rather than feeling like a nobody. Sometimes I forget people actually look up to me, because I find myself becoming my own worst enemy when I get in my head to much. I've been away too long, I'm ready to get to know everyone again. Thank you all for reading. - Adam Dahlberg 2018

Nobodies are those always on the path to be somebody everyday. 
#Nobodies
